gomodel:SYNGO_4635  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2. Confocal immunofluorescence staining of cultured hippocampal neurons demonstrating that Vezatin was localized in neurons positive for the neuronal marker Tubb3 and colocalized with the excitatory postsynaptic marker PSD-95 but not with the excitatory presynaptic marker synapsin 1.\n\nfurther functional studies show that a knockdown of Vezatin affects GluA1 phosphorylation via PKA (suggestive of postsynaptic localization rather than presynaptic, which supports the observations from Figure 2). Experimental description: Immunofluorescence staining was performed on cultures hippocampal neurons from mice. M&M info on Immunofluorescence staining of human brain tissue reflects methods for Figure 7.\n\n\"Immunofluorescence staining\nThe immunofluorescence procedures were described previously [20, 28]. The mice were rapidly euthanized, and mouse brain tissues were fixed with 4% paraformaldehyde for 24 h; the human brain tissues were also fixed with 4% paraformaldehyde for 24 h.\"\n\n\"In cultured hippocampal neurons, immunofluorescence staining showed that vezatin (green) was expressed in neurons positive for the neuronal marker beta-Tubulin III (Tubb3) (red) and colocalized with the excitatory postsynaptic marker postsynaptic density protein 95 (PSD-95) (purple) (Fig. 2a) but not with the presynaptic marker synapsin 1 (purple) (Fig. 2b). \"\n\nAntibodies described in this annotation;\nmouse vezatin antibody (Santa Cruz Biotechnology; 1:100)\nmouse Tubb3 antibody (Proteintech; 1:400)\nrabbit PSD-95 antibody (Abcam; 1:200)\nrabbit Synapsin 1 antibody (Novus; 1:200)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-05-05" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4635" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

